HEADWORD: Ghoul
<hw>Ghoul</hw> <pr>(g⟦oomac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>gh⟦omac⟧l</ets> an imaginary sylvan demon, supposed to devour men
and animals: cf. Ar. <ets>gh⟦umac⟧l</ets>, F. <ets>goule</ets>.]</ety>
<def>An imaginary evil being among Eastern nations, which was supposed
to feed upon human bodies.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>ghole</asp>
.]</altsp> <rj><au>Moore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ghoulish</ent>⟦br⟧
